Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the design and control of an aerial manipulator for contact inspection, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the closed-loop dynamics and controller design for the aerial manipulator. 
- cs.ROB (Robotics and Automation) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and control of a robotic system. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the control of a multirotor aerial vehicle. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions NDT (Non-Destructive Testing) inspection, which may involve computer vision techniques.
